The Audit Committee met seven times in 2023.

The committee assists and advises the SB with (i) the performance of its duties in relation to the integrity and quality of ING's financial reporting, (ii) the effectiveness of ING's internal risk management and control systems in relation to financial reporting and (iii) the preparation of the discussions within and the decisions of the SB on such matters.

The Audit Committee addressed, among other things, the following recurring topics:

- · The quarterly results and the related press releases, the interim accounts and the financial statements, the Annual Report, the 6-K and 20-F forms, and the SOx Act 404 Report;
- · Judgemental accounting topics;
- · Financial reporting, including the quarterly results;
- · Key audit matters, as included in the auditors' reports;
- · (The approval of) the external auditor's audit plan/engagement letter/independence and fees;
